‘You don’t teach kids to grapple hold of someone, just pull them. That’s happening more and more. Hopefully we will get some decisions that will stop people doing it.’

Monk, in charge at Swansea, wants referees to be handed clearer rules so they can act when defenders pull back attackers at set pieces.

‘Referees need to be more consistent but the rules can be clearer too,’ Monk said. ‘It’s an art to defend and to take contact away completely with everybody marking zonal would take away from the game.

