‘But there’s a line you don’t cross and it is making sure the line is clear. That line is when you have been beaten by the man, he’s got away from you and you are pulling his shirt and grabbing his arms. That’s what you have to stamp out. The refs need to be given a clear rule as it would be an easier decision for them.’

